<p><b>"An Occurrence at Owl Creek Bridge"</b> (sometimes called "An Incident at Owl Creek Bridge") is a <a href="/wiki/Short_story" title="Short story">short story</a> by <a href="/wiki/Ambrose_Bierce" title="Ambrose Bierce">Ambrose Bierce</a>. It was originally published in 1890, and first collected in Bierce's 1891 book, <i>Tales of Soldiers and Civilians</i>. The story is famous for its irregular time sequence and <a href="/wiki/Twist_ending" title="Twist ending">twist ending</a>.</p>
